        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Socket is the default adapter for client, and is having issues \/ connecting to the majority of sites. The simple code below triggers an exception that returns an empty string and thus the exception is thrown on Response::fromString which is called by Socket. Strangely it can handle a connection to google.com. So, I'm guessing there's a header that's missing or conversely, is present and confusing it?\r\n\r\n$this->httpClient = new Client;\r\n$this->httpClient->setUri('http:\/\/framework.zend.com');\r\n$response = $this->httpClient->send();\r\n"
        },
